Package: ggmagnitude
Title: Create Visual Magnitude Plots on a Colored Scale
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Horacio", "Chacon Torrico", email = "hchacont@uw.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools to create magnitude plots, primarily using a logarithmic scale, 
    for visual representation of data across wide-ranging orders of magnitude. 
    These plots offer an intuitive way to compare and understand the relative scale 
    of various data points using color gradients and positioned labels.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: 
    ggplot2,
    dplyr,
    scales,
    ggrepel,
    rlang
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
